$ Perl operator // (slash slash)

The *slash slash* operator in perl returns the left side value *if* it is defined, otherwise it returns the right side value.

This differs from the → development/languages/Perl/operators/bar_bar[|| operator] in that the `|| operator` checks
for truth rather than definendness.

`$x //= 'value'` assignes 'value' to `$x` unless $x is defined.

The slash slash operator comes in handy, for example, when handling → development/languages/Perl/modules/DBD/SQLite/nulls[null values] with one of the → development/languages/Perl/modules/DBD[DBD modules].

gh|about-perl|/operators/slash_slash.pl||

sa:
  → development/languages/Perl/operators/[Perl operators]
